
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-ospf-ospfv3-autoconfig-15.txt'>
    <title>"OSPFv3 Auto-Configuration", Acee Lindem, Jari Arkko</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-ospf-ospfv3-autoconfig-15.txt</link>
    <description>OSPFv3 is a candidate for deployments in environments where auto- configuration is a requirement.  One such environment is the IPv6 home network where users expect to simply plug in a router and have it automatically use OSPFv3 for intra-domain routing.  This document describes the necessary mechanisms for OSPFv3 to be self-configuring. This document updates RFC 5340 by relaxing the HelloInterval/ RouterDeadInterval checking during OSPFv3 adjacency formation and adding hysteresis to the update of self-originated Link State Advertisements (LSAs).</description>
    <dc:date>2015-02-10T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
